            <div class='content-div__content'>
                <h2>Goal</h2>
                <p>Provide a style framework for Ember apps that is</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>lightweight</li>
                    <li>customizable</li>
                    <li>maintainable and easy to update</li>
                    <li>expandable for larger projects</li>
                    <li>simpler than Bootstrap or Foundation</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Dirk's Style Template provides</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>instructions on how to get the code into your project</li>
                    <li>{{link-to 'a responsive header for your app' 'header'}}</li>
                </ul>
                <h2 class='mt40'>Who and What For</h2>
                <p>Ideal for</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>rapid prototyping</li>
                    <li>quickly setting up custom styles</li>
                    <li>smallish Ember apps (yet easy to expand)</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Shortcomings</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>not as comprehensive as Bootstrap or Foundation</li>
                </ul>
                <h2 class='mt40'>How To</h2>
                <p>First browse this site and {{globals.githubDirksStyleTemplateLink}} to learn how Dirk's Style Framework works and is setup.</p>
                <p>Install depent and optional Ember Addons.</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>All dependent and optional Ember Addons are listed below under JS Framework.</li>
                    <li>Click the link to their Github page and follow all their installation instructions.</li>
                    <li>See this site's {{globals.githubNpmPackageLink}}</li>
                </ol>
                <p>Add the styles / components / helpers to your site.</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>For the style sheets:</li>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Install and setup {{globals.emberCliSassLink}}.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <li>For helpers and components:</li>
                    <ul>
                        <li>CLI generate the desired helper or component files.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <li>Access Dirk's Style Framework code:</li>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Fork, download or browse the project code from {{globals.githubDirksStyleTemplateLink}}.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <li>Copy and paste the {{globals.githubStylesDir}},  {{globals.githubComponentsDir}} or {{globals.githubHelpersDir}} code into your files.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
