                <h2>Normalize and Reset</h2>
                <p>{{globals.githubNormalizeLink}} v8.0.1 is imported first. It is slightly modified: {{globals.githubStylesNormalizeLink}}.</p>
                <p>A local {{globals.githubStylesResetLink}} is imported next.</p>

                <h2 class='mt40'>Variables</h2>
                <p>{{globals.githubStylesVariablesLink}} defines almost all style settings.</p>

                <h2 class='mt40'>App</h2>
                <p>{{globals.githubStylesAppLink}} defines HTML block elements as well as the site's header, content, and footer styles with the exception of buttons and inputs, which have their own files.</p>

                <h2 class='mt40'>Imports</h2>
                <p>Each import contains only definitions for the specific element(s) or component implied by its title.</p>

                <h2 class='mt40'>Project Specific Styles</h2>
                <p>styles/_project.scss is a single file to keep definitions for very small projects. As this file grows consider breaking it into smaller more manageable files.</p>

                <h2 class='mt40'>Helper Classes</h2>
                <p>{{globals.githubStylesHelpersLink}} contains many class definitions of commonly used styles. See {{#link-to 'layout'}}Layout{{/link-to}} and the file itself for class definitions and usage.</p>

                <h2 class='mt40'>BEM</h2>
                <p><b>B</b>lock <b>E</b>lement <b>M</b>odifier naming convention is used in the .scss files.</p>
                <p>See {{globals.bem101}} for a nice introduction.</p>
                <h3>Block component</h3>
                {{show-code code='.btn {}'}}
                <h3>Element - depends on the block</h3>
                {{show-code code='.btn__price {}'}}
                <h3>Modifier - changes the style</h3>
                {{show-code code='.btn--warn {}
.btn__price--success {}'}}
                <h3>With SASS we can:</h3>
                {{show-code code='.btn {
  @at-root #{&}__price { }
  @at-root #{&}--warn { }
  @at-root #{&}__price--success { }
}'}}
